";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Bas de Baar";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2852:"<p>I am fascinated by  temporary social systems.  People in groups. In clusters. Small groups. Large groups. Global groups. Virtual groups. </p>
<p>But only <a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/three-balances-for-resilient-groups-why-every-group-will-collapse-4041.html">groups that last for a short amount of time</a>. Like projects.</p>
<p>I am hooked on resilience in social systems. How do groups cope with disturbances while remaining their function?</p>
<p>I choose to focus on <a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/the-essential-role-of-culture-in-projects-2604.html">culture</a> and <a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/no-more-dharmas-3671.html">identity</a> and their role in <a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/the-big-concept-overview-map-how-stuff-fits-together-4370.html">interaction and collaboration</a> as mechanism for resilience.</p>
<p>Projects are ideal case studies for temporary social systems. </p>
<p>And within the notion of projects I focus on two specific types:</p>
<h2>1. Projects as interventions in a larger host organization.</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/rsz_tempsystem2.jpg"><img src="http://www.basdebaar.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/rsz_tempsystem2-300x180.jpg" alt="" title="rsz_tempsystem2" width="300" height="180" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-4396" /></a><br />
<em>(click on image to enlarge)</em></p>
<h2>2. Projects that are the combination of a pool of global flexible talent on one side and facilitating containers with a purpose on the other side.</h2>
<p>Please read &#8220;<a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/new-trends-in-the-project-ecosystem-3360.html">New Trends In The Project Ecosystem</a>&#8221; for full details. But in short:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/rsz_1tempsystem.jpg"><img src="http://www.basdebaar.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/rsz_1tempsystem-300x167.jpg" alt="" title="rsz_1tempsystem" width="300" height="167" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-4397" /></a><br />
<em>(click on image to enlarge)</em></p>
<ul>
<li>the combination of Internet tools to work mobile and an independent workforce, one that has no full-time engagement with an employer, creates an extreme mobile pool of knowledge workers;</li>
<li>a company in this model has a small core by itself and attracts workforce and third parties on a project to project or product to product base. In this way organizations are nothing more than an empty vehicle to facilitate the execution of a large set of temporary endeavors;</li>
<li>digital marketplaces match the previous two categories together.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://www.basdebaar.com/intervention-and-pool-container-4395.html">Intervention. And Pool-Container. Two Types Of Temporary Social Systems.</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.basdebaar.com">Project Shrink</a></p>
