<p>As Dave explains&#8230;</p>
<p><em>&#8220;Last November while I was a Øredev 2010, I had the great fortune to meet up with Kathy Compton and Thierry Holweck  from the band Panda Transport. They had come to Øredev to perform and give a few presentations as part of the Xtra track. While my initial interest was in Kathy&#8217;s presentation on how to use the voice and body language as a performer, the more I learned about Panda Transport, the more interested I became in the idea that artists composing music across a wide geographic range (Kathy is in the US and Thierry is in France) may not be that different from folks in IT who are working with distributed or offshore teams.  Perhaps there is something IT can learn from the music business to help us work through some of our geographic/cultural challenges. This two part interview with Kathy covers those topics than more. It is one of my favorite interviews that I have done. And if you don&#8217;t know what a Yurt is, you are about to find out…&#8221;</em></p>
